details: Explore award-winning takes on beloved white varietals with this flavorful 3-pack. Featuring wines from regions in Italy, France, and California, this selection includes fresh Sauvignon Blanc, smooth Chardonnay, and crisp Pinot Grigio. These whites are wonderful complements to seafood, chicken and pork, and veggie-based dishes. F09305	2020 Maison Gourmand Cotes du Gascogne Sauvignon Blanc Sip and savor silver medal winning flavor with 2020 Maison Gourmand Sauvignon Blanc. Uniquely fermented in stainless steel tanks, this wine is then aged on fine lees for several months allowing it to develop in flavor and rounded structure. This carefully crafted Sauvignon Blanc exhibits a beautiful emerald color along with notes of exotic fruit and delicate white flowers. Persistent citrus on the palate offers cheek pinching zest you won’t soon forget, especially when this white’s enjoyed chilled. 	 Yvon Mau. France. 12% ABV	 N01380	2020 Cannery Row Cellars Chardonnay Uncork a bottle and enjoy every sip of silver medal winning flavor with California’s Cannery Row Chardonnay. This bouncy and fresh white balances fruit notes of rich, custard-style lemon flavor, nectarine, and white flowers with oaky butterscotch and caramel. This is a great cocktail wine because it doesn't need food, but it also pairs beautifully with seafood and the lighter side of chicken and pork dishes. Cannery Row Cellars. California. 13% ABV F09315	2020 Ammannati Pinot Grigio I.G.T.  Enjoy Sicilian silver medal winning flavor with 2020 Ammannati Pinot Grigio I.G.T., a crisp classic Pinot Grigio. The precise selection of grapes makes for this wine’s golden yellow color and distinctive aromas of exotic fruits. Savor bright and fresh pineapple and grapefruit as they elegantly grace your nose. Lovely as a chilled aperitif, this delightful white wine also pairs perfectly with chicken or fish. Hemispheres. Italy. 12% ABV

While planning a special evening, you’ll want the perfect wines on hand to share with your partner. Including award-winning bottles, this 3-pack is sure to impress! You’ll uncork a beautiful Bordeaux red blend, a savory Cabernet Sauvignon, and a fruity sparkling rosé—all wonderful sipped on their own or paired with meals like pan-seared steak, grilled halibut, fried chicken, and more.   F09304	2020 Beau Palais Bordeaux Rouge  Uncork Beau Palais Bordeaux Rouge an elegant gold medal-winning red blend that could only come from the prestigious wine region of Bordeaux. Composed of Merlot and Cabernet Sauvignon, this wine has a deep red color that is bound to entice once poured. On the nose, there are intense notes of red fruit that carry into the palate. Along with its fruity flavor, the palate is supple with strong tannins that shape its character.This wine is the ideal accompaniment to hardy and comforting meals that center around meats such as game, lamb, or beef. Hemispheres. France. 13% ABV F09309	2020 Casa De La Luna Reserva de Selección Cabernet Sauvignon Experience 2020 Casa De La Luna Reserva de Selección Cabernet Sauvignon, a juicy gold medal winning Cab from Chile’s renowned Maule Valley. Enjoy a complex nose of spice, red currant, and earthy tobacco leaf. The palate unfolds with bell pepper-flecked ripe plums, cherry, hints of charcoal, and nicely toasted spices, then finished with a subtle, sweet-candy flavor. A wonderful match for flame-grilled cowboy steaks or a meaty bowl of pasta Bolognese. Hemispheres. Chile. 13% ABV N01293	George Phillips Cellars Signature Reserve No. 1764 Sparkling Brut Rosé Uncork award-winning George Phillips Cellars Signature Reserve No. 1764 Sparkling Brut Rosé and take in juicy notes of raspberry and red fruits with splashes of bright citrus. Floral on the nose, this wine offers pronounced fruitiness on the palate, lifted by fine bubbles. The finish is crisp, smooth, and refreshing. George Phillips Cellars Signature Reserve No. 1764 Sparkling Brut Rosé is delightful on its own and when served with white meats and a variety of vegetables. It’s the ideal companion to brunch dishes, too. Serve chilled. George Phillips Cellars. California. 11.5% ABV

Enjoy warm weather occasions while sipping on fabulous, fruity Rosé! This 3-pack features elegant, award-winning takes on the beloved pink drink from vineyards across France. These wines are wonderful companions to grilled chicken, salads, veggie skewers, shellfish, and more. R10180	2020 Bruno Lafon Grenache Rosé Discover 2020 Bruno Lafon Grenache Rosé, a fresh rosé awarded 94-point Platinum at the 2021 Sommelier Challenge International Wine Competition. This Grenache-driven rosé displays a fruity-floral bouquet, led by citrus fruits and white flowers. Beautifully textured with layers of flavor, its palate offers juicy notes of strawberry and nectarine with yeasty hints of baker’s dough. Enjoy with seafood and shellfish, salads, and light pasta dishes. Bruno Lafon. France. 12.5% ABV R10227	2020 Bernard Magrez Rosé Experience French finesse with multiple award-winning 2020 Bernard Magrez Rosé. Pale pink in color with a lighthearted feel, this rosé is a pleasure to drink. Delicate flavors of raspberry and red fruit join tart notes of gooseberry for a refreshing finish. Made from Grenache grapes, it is dry with moderately high acidity. Enjoy 2020 Bernard Magrez Rosé chilled with crisp vegetable salads as well as grilled fish, chicken, or pork.  Bernard Magrez. France. 12.5% ABV R10221	2020 Le Bosq Vin Rosé A bright and balanced French rosé, 2020 Le Bosq Vin Rosé is the latest gold medal winning vintage in a line of award-winning, customer favorite wines. Enjoy red fruit flavors with hints of grenadine. Raspberry and cranberry notes carry into the palate, which strikes just the right balance between fresh acidity and round structure, leaving a clean finish. Serve with cheese plates, salads, lobster rolls, pizza, and grilled burgers. Le Bosq. France. 12% ABV

Discover robust, fruit-driven reds with layers of complexity in this 3-pack, demonstrating how combining different grapes can lead to delicious results. Fans of California red wines are sure to enjoy these award-winning blends, which pair splendidly to barbecued meats and veggies, hearty pasta, nachos and pizza, and much more. N01340	2020 MYTH Red Blend This award-winning 2018 MYTH Red Blend is a big, flavorful wine with bold dark fruit aromas of fresh black cherry and rhubarb. This red unfolds to dizzying notes of vanilla and mocha. Made from an exciting blend of beloved California grapes, this red blend shows round tannins and a medium body. Uncork this red blend as you enjoy a delicate pork dish at home or bring it with you to a barbecue of sweetly glazed meats. First Crush Vineyards. California. 13% ABV N01366	2018 Jenna Red Blend From a winery well-known in northern California for its well-balanced flavors and vinicultural tradition comes the gold medal winning 2018 Jenna Red Blend. This red blend is fruit-forward with prominent notes of dark fruit. The first sniff will greet you with subtle notes of raspberry. As the wine moves to the tongue, further fruity notes of strawberry and blackberry will be accentuated by the wine's supple tannins and moderate acidity. Jenna Wines. California. 13.5% ABV N01302	Bayshore Vintners Red Blend Enjoy a succulent silver medal winning blend of six grapes including Merlot and Zinfandel.  This medium to full-bodied wine makes a bold statement from first whiff, with aromas of ripe red and dark fruit bursting forth. A juicy palate displays black cherries, blueberries, and brambly blackberry underscored with pepper. Sweet vanilla meets subtle hints of chocolate on the finish, which is wonderfully smooth.  Bayshore Vintners. California. 13.9% ABV

Fresh, herbaceous, and thirst-quenching, Sauvignon Blanc is a crowd-pleasing choice for a white wine. Enjoy award-winning takes on the popular varietal from Chile, California, and France with this 3-pack. These wines are just as tasty sipped on their own as they are paired to light seasonal dishes.   R10209	2020 De La Rougerie Sauvignon Blanc From the South of France, 2020 De La Rougerie Sauvignon Blanc is a crisp and approachable white wine with gold medal winning merit. Vibrant and full of flavor, this wine expresses citrus notes accompanied by green apple and subtle hints of exotic fruits. Influences from the region’s terroir impart minerality and floral touches on the palate, which leaves a deliciously thirst-quenching finish. Enjoy it on its own or alongside soft cheeses, baked fish, grilled zucchini, fried chicken, and pea soup. Benoit Valerie Calvet. France. 11.5% ABV N01346	2020 George Phillips Cellars Reserve Selection No. 043 Sauvignon Blanc Experience refreshing California craftsman ship when you uncork a bottle of gold medal winning George Phillips Cellars Reserve Selection No. 043 Sauvignon Blanc. This satisfying white wine has a rich flavor with aromatic ripe fruits. Enjoy robust notes of citrus and herbs with a fresh creaminess. There is bright acidity yet a traditional dry feel on the palate. Perfect pairings include buttery seafood, creamy pasta, and spice-filled cheeses. George Phillips Cellars. California. 13% ABV R10086	2020 Tripantu Sauvignon Blanc Reserve Maule Valley Enjoy a brilliant display of Chilean winemaking in 2020 Tripantu Sauvignon Blanc Reserve Maule Valley. This wine garnered 94-point platinum status at the 2021 Monterey International Wine Competition. A unique combination of currant, asparagus, and orange blossom flavor notes create an exciting tasting experience for white wine enthusiasts. Medium-bodied and balanced, this Sauvignon Blanc has crisp acidity transitioning to a short but refreshing finish.  Explore with ideal pairings like fish, oysters, and salads. Terraustral Wines. Chile. 13.5% ABV

productName: Bold Red Wine California Selections Trio
details: Discover rich, fruit-forward flavor from vineyards across the Golden State. This 3-pack offers delicious, uniquely Californian takes on popular reds, including jammy Zinfandel, spicy Syrah, and luscious Merlot. These selections pair perfectly with grilled foods, pizza and pasta, pork carnitas, and hearty dishes. 2018 Pioneer Town Shiraz Sip the spirit of discovery with award-winning 2018 Pioneer Town Shiraz, an easy-drinking, fruity, and spicy California red. Uncork this dry, medium-bodied Shiraz and get ready to embark on a delicious journey. The weather in San Joaquin Valley, California is hot which causes the Shiraz grapes to ripen fully with lower amounts of tannin and very ripe fruit flavors. Blackberries, cassis, and a little hint of spice can be found as the wine unravels on your palate. This Shiraz’s dark fruity flavors pair well with grilled meats and vegetables; think country barbecue. 13.5% ABV 2018 Fair Oaks Ranch Zinfandel The latest vintage of Fair Oaks’ platinum medal-winning Zinfandel is packed with rich berry jam flavors and hints of black pepper and anise. A nice touch of acidity creates a clean, food-friendly finish.  Originating from Europe where it is known by other names, such as Primitivo in Italy and Tribidrag in Croatia, Zinfandel thrives in warm, sunny climates. Expect a jammy, black-fruited quality to this wine, which also shows off a spicy tobacco finish.  We love to recommend Zinfandel for a barbecue—its boldness is often a match for grilled foods, but it’s also smooth enough to enjoy on its own.  14.5% ABV 2018 Sierra Trails Merlot 2018 Sierra Trails Merlot hails from the wine-famous regions of California, in a region with conditions that were seemingly created for the sole purpose of creating wine. This Merlot's fruity flavors are intense, but not overwhelming. Its aromas are of cherry, blackberry, and vanilla. Its body is moderate with supple tannins and moderate acidity. Pair it with a meaty pizza or sautéed veggies.	 13% ABV

Smooth, easy-drinking Chardonnay is a Golden State specialty! This tasty 3-pack offers award-winning takes on the classic white varietal, ranging from crisp and refreshing to oaked and creamy. Delicious on their own, these wines pair well to chicken, seafood, and veggie-centric dishes.    N01381	2020 Bayshore Vintners Chardonnay Enjoy a celebration of California’s most-planted white grape in 2020 Bayshore Vintners Chardonnay. Fresh and fruity, this white wine carries flavorful notes of ripe golden apple and pear with refreshing hints of citrus. The finish is crisp yet smooth and wonderfully easy-drinking. 2020 Bayshore Vintners Chardonnay is perfect for any celebration and complements soft cheeses, seafood, vegetable risotto, and lightly-herbed chicken or pork. Bayshore Vintners. California. 13% ABV N01385	2020 Windsor Hills Barrel Fermented ChardonnayGet lost in the tropical landscapes of this gold medal winning 2020 Windsor Hill Chardonnay, as citrus and vanilla tasting notes melt onto your palate. Barrel fermented for an extra velvety texture, this rich Chardonnay has a soft, balanced mouthfeel and hints of a caramel aftertaste. The next time you bring out the pork tenderloin and potatoes, make sure you grab the 2020 Windsor Hill Chardonnay as well. Saddlehorn Cellars. California. 13.5% ABV N01374 	2019 Stone & Glass Chardonnay Inspired by a famous beach in California that's littered with smooth, sparkling sea glass, Stone & Glass is a rich silver medal winning Chardonnay that offers up enticing flavors and aromas of golden apple and pear. Its crisp texture and long, complex finish will delight with soft cheese or grilled fish. Jenna Wines. California. 13% ABV

Uncork savory reds (like Bordeaux blends and Cabernet Sauvignon) and easy-sipping whites (like smooth Chardonnay and fruity sparkling rosé). These wines are wonderful sipped on their own or paired with meals. A wonderful match for flame-grilled cowboy steaks or a meaty bowl of pasta Bolognese. Hemispheres. Chile. 13% ABV N01365	2018 Jenna Pinot Noir Discover award winning excellence in 2018 Jenna Pinot Noir a refreshingly aromatic red wine with fruit notes that mingled with hints of spice and earth in enticing layers of complexity. Wild strawberries and brambly berries are underscored with dried flowers, herbs, and a touch of allspice. The palate is structured, dry, and medium-bodied, offering a round and luscious mouthfeel. This varietal plays well with many foods, and 2018 Jenna Pinot Noir is a great choice to uncork with grilled or roasted chicken, seared salmon and tuna, and charcuterie. Jenna Wines. California. 13.8% ABV F09302	2020 Beau Palais Bordeaux Blanc Like a morning spent in the subregion or Bordeaux, France, this white feels sunkissed and brimming with freshness. Made from 100% Sauvignon Blanc grapes, this award-winng Bordeaux Blanc was crafted in Entre-deux-Mers. Gorgeous in the glass, this wine pours to display a lovely pale gold hue and delicate aromas of citrus and peaches. The palate unfolds with ripe fruit notes and minerality. The finish is a beautiful citrus ideal with tapas, fish, and white meats. Hemispheres. France. 12.5% ABV F09298	2019 Flores Chardonnay  Enjoy an exciting New World take on the world’s most popular white varietal with 2019 Flores Reserva Chardonnay, a silver medal-winning medium-bodied white wine from Chile. This lovely Chardonnay opens with an aromatic bouquet of pineapple, banana, and toasted almond. The palate is balanced with fruity yet smooth flavor notes that leave a long and creamy aftertaste. Enjoy alongside seafood and shellfish, as well as creamy dishes like rich pasta, potato salad, and corn chowder.		 Cremaschi Furlotti. Make the season a sweet one with this 3-pack of off-dry wines from Italy and California. You’ll uncork delightful, easy-drinking takes on Moscato that are delicious on their own or with light desserts such as cheesecake, berry tarts, and fresh fruit. N01371	2020 Snickerdoodle Moscato Discover the pride of California wineries in this mouthwatering Moscato with silver medal winning merit. This thirst-quenching Moscato carries deep aromas of peach, jasmine, and rose petals. Its smooth tannins will help guide its robust flavors and aromas, allowing for a full appreciation of its intense flavors. Enjoy with a light salad, fruit, or just on its own! Free Flight Cellars. California. 12.5% ABV R10399	Abbazia "La Tartaruga" Moscato Pavia I.G.T. European mountain air and Mediterranean ocean breezes combine on the Abbazia family winery, where this tasty Moscato heralds from. This wine is a sweet treat for anyone, floating delectable flavors of honey and peach over the light body and satin texture of the wine. The Abbazia Moscato Pavia is a drink for indulging your sweet tooth. Drink this wine all on its own, or pair with a light dessert. Abbazia Winery. Italy. 6% ABV R10398	Abbazia Asti Spumante D.O.C.G. Discover a light and distinctive Italian wine produced in Piedmont, the same region that produces coveted truffles, cheeses and meats. This multiple award winning moscato-based sparkling wine carries a D.O.C.G. rating, the highest level of wine certification from the Italian National Government, ensuring that this wine is of the utmost quality. Enjoy with pairings including sponge cake, soufflés, fruit salads, and strudels. Abbazia Winery. Italy. 7.5% ABV

Explore award-winning takes on beloved red varietals with this flavorful 3-pack. Featuring wines from regions in California and Argentina, this selection includes savory Cabernet Sauvignon, rich Malbec, and bright Pinot Noir. These reds are wonderful complements to aged cheeses, grilled meats, roasted vegetables, and more.   F09312	2020 Casa de Pinaculo Malbec Pour and enjoy silver medal winning flavor with 2020 Casa de Pinaculo Malbec from one of Argentina’s most celebrated wine regions. Once poured, admire the wine’s dark black color and bright violet hues. Take a sip for aromas of strawberries, cherries, and vanilla with balanced acidity and silky tannins. This wine is delicious when served with a seared rib-eye fresh from the grill or a roasted leg of lamb. Hemispheres. Argentina. 13.8% ABV N01278	2018 Pioneer Town Cabernet Sauvignon Sip the spirit of discovery with 2018 Pioneer Town Cabernet Sauvignon, a classic silver medal winning California Cab. Uncork this dry, full-bodied red and get ready to embark on a deliciously rewarding journey. You’ll pick up concentrated flavors of blackberry and black currant, which meet hints of cedar and mocha, representing the wine’s oak-aging. Serve this Cab with porterhouse steak, lamb stew, braised short ribs, grilled portobello burgers, and aged cheddar or gouda cheeses. Hemispheres. California. 12.4% ABV N01287	2018 Bayshore Vintners Pinot Noir Experience 2018 Bayshore Vintners Pinot Noir, a gold medal winning California Pinot with ripe fruit flavor and smooth delivery. Red fruits abound in this light-bodied red wine displaying lively aromatics. Strawberry and cherry notes carry into the palate, which offers bright acidity with touches of dried herbs. Hints of allspice and vanilla from oak aging round out this easy-drinking Pinot Noir, which is quite versatile with foods. It pairs beautifully with main courses consisting of roasted chicken, mushroom risotto, and pan-fried sea bass. Bayshore Vintners. California. 13.9% ABV

Dreaming of a wine Christmas? Count down to the holiday by sipping your way through different varietals. This limited-edition advent calendar contains two mini bottles each of 12 delicious wines from regions across California. Will you pop open a crisp white? Or perhaps a velvety red blend? Treat yourself and order this merry 24-pack before it sells out!   American Vintners. California. 187 ml.

Kick back, relax, and uncork easy-sipping wines from Europe and California. This flavorful trio includes two savory reds and one refreshing white that are perfect for enjoying during warm weather occasions. Delicious on their own, these award-winning bottles also pair to pizza, cheeses, and grilled meats, chicken, and veggies.    R10071	2018 Primasera Sangiovese Puglia I.G.T. Fans of rich, Italian reds are sure to enjoy silver medal winning 2018 Primasera Sangiovese I.G.T. This Sangiovese was crafted by Castellani, an award-winning family winery that has been producing distinctive wines since 1903. An intense ruby red color in the glass, this harmonious wine opens with a rich bouquet of plum and bramble fruit flavors along with aromas of strawberry, violet, and pepper. Its high acidity and light-moderate tannins complement tomato and meat-based dishes, so this red is a perfect companion to pizza, pasta, and lasagna. Castellani S.p.A. Italy. 12.5% ABV N01307	2020 Lone Cardinal Cabernet Sauvignon  From a line inspired by the majestic bird, platinum medal winning 2020 Lone Cardinal Cabernet Sauvignon offers bold character that stands on its own.  Open it ahead of time to let the aromas and tasting notes of black currant and black cherry take flight. Each sip delivers generous fruit flavor with hints of dried herbs and vanilla wrapped up in a warm, lingering finish. This wine is sure to sing when served with flavorful meals like roast leg of lamb, char-grilled cheeseburgers, vegetable skewers, and truffled brie cheese. Hemispheres. California. 13.8% ABV F09305	2020 Maison Gourmand Cotes du Gascogne Sauvignon Blanc Sip and savor silver medal winning flavor with 2020 Maison Gourmand Sauvignon Blanc. Uniquely fermented in stainless steel tanks, this wine is then aged on fine lees for several months allowing it to develop in flavor and rounded structure. This carefully crafted Sauvignon Blanc exhibits a beautiful emerald color along with notes of exotic fruit and delicate white flowers. Persistent citrus on the palate offers cheek pinching zest you won’t soon forget, especially when this white’s enjoyed chilled. 	 Yvon Mau. France. 12% ABV

Enjoy a mix of red and white wines made from organic grapes. Full of flavor, this 6-pack offers delicious selections from vineyards in Italy, Spain, and California. You’ll get a taste of juicy, food-friendly reds, like Montepulciano, and fresh, fruity whites including Prosecco. These wines are wonderful sipped on their own and paired with a variety of seasonal dishes.    R09883	2019 Merveille de Vignes Organic Monastrell-Merlot Blend by EthicDrinks Made from organic grapes, 2019 Merveille de Vignes Organic Monastrell-Merlot Blend is a gold medal winner that is as good in the glass as it is good for the Earth. Hailing from Spain, this blend is plump with enticing aromas of plum, black fruits, licorice, and spices lead to a satisfying finish with every sip. Easy-drinking yet elegant, this vegan wine was awarded an impressive 90-point Gold Medal by Andreas Larsson, ranked among the World’s Best Sommeliers. Enjoy alongside spicy meats, beef stir-fry, pizza, pasta, and a variety of cheeses. Ethic Drinks.  Spain. 14.5% ABV R10193	2020 StraBIOrdante Organic Montepulciano d’Abruzzo D.O.C. Enjoy a classic Italian varietal with silver medal winning credentials in 2020 StraBIOrdante Organic Montepulciano, a lovely, medium-bodied red wine. It is made from organic grapes grown in vineyards situated along the Adriatic coast of Italy.  Hints of rich red fruits are underscored with warm, enveloping aromas that call to the senses. On the palate, pronounced fruitiness is met with dried herbs. Strong tannic structure lends a pleasantly persistent finish.  Enjoy with perfect pairings such as lamb kabobs, rich lasagnas, baked salmon, and aged cheeses. Cantina Etrusca. Italy. 13% ABV C01093	2019 Puente de la Vega Racies Organic Garnacha Not sure what would pair best with dinner? Slowly unravel the versatile sweet, salty, and spice flavors of this silver medal winning Organic Spanish Garnacha. On the nose are fresh and floral red fruits, along with sweet and salty spices, bay leaf, and menthol. The notes enter softly and produce a long and fruity finish with well-balanced tannins. Enjoy this 100% organic Garnacha Tintorera on its own or beside fresh vegetables and grilled red meats. Bodega Venta La Vega. Spain. 14.5% ABV R09773	Calvari Organic White Blend  Discover a silver medal winning white wine blend made with organic grapes and dry farmed from the historic wine regions of Northern Italy. This Italian White Blend carries smooth scents of a floral bouquet paired with fruity flavors of peach and apricot. Honey undertones make for a smooth, delicious finish. The wine is also vegan friendly and gluten free. Pair this wine with salads, vegan and vegetarian dishes to poultry with light sauces or grilled fish for a delectable match. Castellani S.p.A. Italy. 12% ABV N01306	2019 Della Flora Organic Chardonnay Discover a classic California take on a popular white varietal in silver medal winning 2019 Della Flora Organic Chardonnay. This dry, medium-bodied white wine is made from organic grapes. A slightly sweet nose hints at this Chardonnay’s rich, voluptuous flavor, bursting with citrus and orchard fruits. Ripe red and yellow apple, pear, lemon, and peach notes mingle. Because it is oak-aged, there are soft vanilla and butterscotch notes on the finish, which is thirst-quenching and smooth. Perfect pairings include rich seafood dishes like lobster. Jenna Wines. California. 13.5% ABV R10266	StraBIOdante Organic Prosecco D.O.C. Unique is an understatement when it comes to multiple award winning StraBIOrdante Organic Prosecco. This Italian Prosecco is elegant and bursting with untraditional flavors crafted to delight. This sparkling Prosecco is clear and bright with a refined perlage. On the nose, this white expresses elegant acacia and banana flower followed by intense notes of apple. On the palate, this bubbling Prosecco is pleasant and harmonious with excellent persistence and good acidity. Enjoy this Italian Prosecco with seafood, savory cheeses, or cured meats.  Corvezzo. Italy. 11.5% ABV

The palate is beautifully layered, displaying rich, ripe flavor notes of fleshy nectarine and delicate biscuit dough. The palate is deliciously juicy with tart acidity and a slightly oily length, leaving a thirst-quenching finish. Perfect pairings include grilled chicken and vegetables, light salads, and either raw or cooked seafood. Lulu Le Français. France. 12% ABV

Fans of red wines are sure to enjoy these award-winning blends from vineyards in France, Italy, and Spain. Pair these wines with equally flavorful dishes, from braised beef to lasagna, tapas to charcuterie. This red blend in particular carries pronounced aromas of ripe cherry and blackberry. Its straightforward aromas carry nicely into more elaborate flavors of plum, leather, and vanilla. Pair this bold red blend with roasted veal or meaty, tomato-based pasta. Yvon Mau. France. 12% ABV R10219	2020 Fauno Red Blend Behold the delicious and ever impressive 2020 Fauno Red Blend awarded a 92-point gold medal at the 2021 Sommelier Challenge. Gently aged in American oak casks—adding a subtly sweet-n-toasty vanilla tone to the wine’s luscious black raspberry, blackberry, and strawberry characters—this is a full-bodied and intense red that’s ready for a hearty meal. Castellani S.p.A. Italy. 13% ABV

Enjoy award-winning takes on the classic red blend with these sumptuous selections, sure to make a statement at any dinner party or special event. Bordeaux reds are prized for their food-friendly nature, pairing well to roasts, grilled meats, savory stews, and a variety of cheeses. R10333	2018 Arnozan Bordeaux Supérieur When searching for a classic red blend that carries both elegance and complexity, we insist you turn to this silver medal winning Arnozan Bordeaux Superieur. productName: The Prisoner Red Blend Red Wine
details: Made with a diverse combination of dark red grapes to bestow distinct quality and character, The Prisoner Red Blend Red Wine is luscious, smooth, and balanced. This California red wine is inspired by the blended wines that were made by Italian immigrants who originally settled in Napa Valley. Crafted with an unlikely mix of zinfandel, cabernet sauvignon, petite sirah, syrah, and merlot, this dark red wine blend features bright aromas of ripe raspberry, vanilla, and coconut. These scents give way to persistent tastes of fresh and dried blackberry and pomegranate with a lingering vanilla flavor. Barrel aging in a combination of old and new, French and American oak barrels brings out the full flavors of this red California wine, making it a great match for grilled meats, especially when they are topped with sweet or tomato-based sauces. Round off a meal with this delicious red wine for a lusciously smooth finish that lingers on the palate. For best taste, store this red wine bottle at room temperature but chill for at least 30 minutes before serving. Please enjoy our wines responsibly. © 2022 The Prisoner Wine Company, Oakville, CA

productName: Kim Crawford Sauvignon Blanc White Wine
details: Kim Crawford Sauvignon Blanc White Wine is fresh and juicy with ripe, tropical flavors of passion fruit, melon, and stone fruit. Each sip of wine reveals classic Marlborough sauvignon blanc aromas of lifted citrus, tropical fruit, and crushed herbs, along with vibrant acidity and plenty of weight and length on the palate. This New Zealand sauvignon blanc is made with grapes specially selected from vineyards in Marlborough's Wairau Valley and the neighboring Awatere Valley. The climate and fast-draining soil in this region offer winemakers a selection of grapes that deliver the consistently flavorful wine for which Kim Crawford is known. Pair this Kim Crawford white wine with fresh oysters, asparagus, lobster, or a light salad. For optimal taste, refrigerate this sauvignon blanc wine for at least two hours then serve chilled. Make it Amazing with Kim Crawford wine. Please enjoy our wines responsibly. © 2022 Constellation Imports, Rutherford, CA USA

productName: Robert Mondavi Pinot Noir Red Wine
details: Robert Mondavi Private Selection Pinot Noir Red Wine is medium bodied with soft tannins and a lingering finish, making it an elegant offering for dinner parties. Fresh flavors of rose petals, strawberry, vibrant cherry and fresh raspberry abound in this pinot noir wine, while hints of Asian spice, sweet tobacco and Madagascar vanilla bean underscore aromas of ripe red cherries and violets. This Robert Mondavi wine is crafted with fruit from California's Central Coast vineyards, where slow ripening in the cool climate by the Pacific Ocean encourages complexity and depth of flavor. The phenomenal grapes produced in the region ultimately create Central Coast wine of the utmost quality, offered by Robert Mondavi Private Selection at a more accessible price. Pair this red table wine with roast meat, poultry or seafood, or serve it at an elegant wine and cheese event. Store this bottle of wine at room temperature, but refrigerate for 30 to 60 minutes before serving at around 60 degrees for optimal taste. details: Meiomi Pinot Noir Red Wine offers unique structure and depth seldom seen in a pinot noir wine. With a rich garnet color and a ruby edge, this dark red wine opens with aromas of jammy fruit and toasty oak. Each sip of this Meiomi wine offers expressive dark berry and juicy strawberry flavors accompanied by toasty mocha and vanilla flavors. The silky texture and balanced acidity of this California red wine make it a perfect tabletop companion to thin crust pizza, so enjoy a glass of wine with your favorite slice. This award-winning Meiomi Pinot Noir offers an unrivaled, full-bodied taste with a lengthy finish, no matter the meal. Serve this bottle of wine at your next get-together for an evocative and memorable impression. For optimal enjoyment of this delicious red wine, store this 750 mL wine bottle at room temperature, but chill it for approximately 60 minutes before serving at 55 to 58 degrees. Cabernet Sauvignon was the first wine Josh Cellars ever made. This is the red wine cabernet that started it all, setting the exacting standards that the brand holds itself to for all varietals. Round and juicy, Josh Cellars Cabernet Sauvignon is a California wine that has flavors of blackberry, toasted hazelnut and cinnamon, complemented by hints of vanilla and toasted oak. Josh Cellars works with California's best growers to source and assemble wine of great character and complexity. Pair this red wine cabernet with well-seasoned meats like beef, pork, or lamb, and indulgent chocolate desserts. The 2016 vintage of Josh Cellars Cabernet Sauvignon is rated as one of the top 5% of wines in the world by Vivino and the 2019 vintage was awarded 91 points by Wine Enthusiast. A Josh Cellars Cabernet Sauvignon bottle of wine is 750 ml and 13.5% ABV. Created by Joseph Carr and named after his father, Josh Cellars makes high-quality, well-balanced, delicious wines that are expressions of gratitude grounded in hard work, high standards and the recognition of others. Josh wine is worth sharing with those who matter.
ingredients: Cabernet Sauvignon Wine, Ripe Blackberry and Cherry Flavors, Spices, Toasted Oak, Sulfites.

This California wine indulges the senses with notes of black cherry, vanilla and mocha and a character all its own. This smooth and rich red blend is medium bodied and pairs with wherever the night may take you. Apothic Red is best enjoyed with plenty of wine glasses to share.  • One 750 mL bottle of Apothic Red Blend Red Wine • Medium body with a smooth finish • Bold and fruit forward with notes of black cherry and dark red fruit • Crowd-pleasing Apothic wine with aromas and notes of mocha and vanilla • Red blend wine from California

details: Matua was the first to produce Sauvignon Blanc in New Zealand, and our passion for the grape hasn't stopped growing. Straight from Marlborough, Matua Marlborough New Zealand Sauvignon Blanc White Wine is a refreshing and energetic wine made for gathering with friends on the pool or patio. A crisp, clean, and slightly citrus personality is the perfect chilled sipper or match for simple appetizers. Since 1974, Matua has crafted a family of fine wines with grapes sourced from New Zealand’s most renowned wine regions – Hawke’s Bay, Marlborough, and Central Otago. From the north to the south, New Zealand’s wine growing regions all offer something unique for a refreshing, chilled experience.
